    takeaway: "Fine-tuning success is a data-*curation* problem, not a volume problem: the base model already learned to think, so SFT is mostly style/format alignment — a few thousand clean, consistent, deduped, on-distribution examples routinely beat hundreds of thousands of noisy ones (LIMA). Build the held-out, production-representative eval set *first* — it defines 'better' and points you at which gaps to fill. Use synthetic data to augment and fill coverage holes, but guard against bias inheritance and model collapse. Dedup between train and eval to prevent leakage, and read the loss curves: falling train loss with flat/rising eval loss means you're memorizing noise — clean the data, don't add epochs.",
    scenario: "Now let's put this to work. Eng scraped 200,000 past tickets — closed conversations, agent replies, everything — and ran SFT overnight. The tuned model came out *worse* than the base: it copies agents' terse, sometimes rude phrasing, contradicts itself between answers, and occasionally leaks another customer's order details it memorized from the training set. The team's instinct is 'we need more data.'\n\nTake a moment: what does everything above tell you? Here's the reasoning, step by step. Fine-tuning makes the model *imitate its training distribution* — so a raw dump of 200k tickets faithfully taught it the terse, sometimes-rude phrasing of the worst agents alongside the best. The self-contradiction? Contradictory ticket pairs taught the model that opposite answers to the same question are both acceptable. The leaked order details? Canned replies and PII duplicated thousands of times let the model *memorize* instead of generalize. So 'we need more data' is exactly backwards — more noisy data makes a worse model, not a bigger one. The fix is to curate *down*: dedup, enforce one consistent output format, remove contradictions, reweight to match production traffic — landing on a few thousand clean examples that will beat 400k raw ones. Hours spent curating 3k pay back more than weeks spent collecting the next 100k. That inversion — quality over volume — is the whole lesson, and the senior signal.",
